<TITLE> Biman flight grounded after engine fire on runway </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 07 (bdnews24.com)  A Bangladesh Biman plane headed for Sylhet was grounded at Zia International Airport on Sunday as one of its engines caught on fire as it was taxiing onto the runway for take-off. A serious incident was averted as the trouble was detected before take-off, an official said. The engine of the F-28 began emitting smoke at around 4:30pm, civil aviation safety service official Nasirullah said. He said fire could not spread as the pilot stopped the engine soon after getting wind of trouble and observing the smoke. A senior airport official said flights bought a long time ago run on the internal routes. These planes each have two engines. The BG-603 flight to Sylhet was cancelled. b
